{
  "narration": "As the sun creeps through the dissipating gloom atop the Corrupted Nexus, Kira, still catching her breath, crouches beside the altar, running a thumb along the battered wolf collar she recovered. Thane, his gaze lingering on the horizon, keeps a watchful eye out for any lingering danger. The quiet peace is interrupted when Kira suddenly stiffens, her hand going to the iron charm at her neck. She blinks, confusion and alarm shadowing her face as her eyes grow distant. \n\nA faint, blue glow flickers along the edge of her sleeve, and you hear a strange, urgent voice--like wind through dead leaves--whispering a message only she can hear. Kira winces, clutching her temples. In a voice strained with worry, she mutters, \"Eirik... I have to go. Elen's in trouble. It's urgent--Harrow's Hollow. Don't wait for me. I'll find you there.\"\n\nWithout waiting for reply, Kira gathers her things--her bow, her pack, the battered collar--and with a haunted, apologetic glance at Eirik and Thane, she sprints down the hill, vanishing into the awakening woods. The iron charm pulses coldly in her absence, a sharp reminder of threats yet unresolved.\n\nThane watches after her, jaw set. \"That was no ordinary message. Something's wrong. We need to finish things here, then find her.\"\n\nYou stand at the heart of the Nexus, victory still fresh, but a new urgency now twists in your chest. Kira's sudden departure and the haunted tone of her warning leave only uncertainty and worry in her wake. The path to Harrow's Hollow--and whatever fate has claimed Commander Elen--awaits you.",
