{
  "narration": "You reach out to call after Kira, but the only answer is the echo of her hurried footsteps, already swallowed by the wilds below the Nexus hill. Thane steps up beside you, his face grim. \"Eirik... she's gone. Whatever message she received, it pulled her out faster than a wolf on a scent.\"\n\nHe glances back at the altar, then at the battered hilltop beginning to brighten with the promise of dawn. \"If she could have waited, she would have. Kira's no fool. She'll want us to follow, but I imagine she's already deep in the pines by now.\"\n\nYou catch your breath, the ache of recent wounds and the weight of exhaustion pressing in. The forest below is silent, no sign of Kira. The only way forward is to trust her skill and heed her warning: Commander Elen is in danger, and Kira is heading to Harrow's Hollow. For now, your party is down to two.\n\nThane rests a reassuring hand on your shoulder. \"We'll find her, Eirik. But first you need to rest, patch yourself up, and make a plan. That's what Kira would want. When you're ready, we can travel to Harrow's Hollow. With any luck, we'll find both her and your commander before whatever darkness is brewing finds them first.\"\n\nThe chill wind stirs the scattered relics of the battle, but the sense of hope lingers. What will you do? Rest, heal your wounds, or set out immediately for Harrow's Hollow?",
