{
  "narration": "As the first rays of dawn struggle through the thinning clouds above the Corrupted Nexus, you let out a dry chuckle. \"Well, the peacefulness was nice while it lasted!\"\n\nThane snorts, a rare grin flickering across his tired face. \"That's the Thornwood for you. Calm for a heartbeat, then it's back to the hunt. If Kira's in danger, she'll want us sharp.\"\n\nHe stoops to check the straps on his battered pack, eyes scanning the ruined altar and the scattered relics one last time. The air still hums with faint pulses of void energy, but the worst of the darkness seems broken.\n\n\"We can take a moment to catch our breath, patch those wounds, or head straight out. But if you want my advice, Eirik, we'll need all our wits and strength before we go chasing after Kira and Commander Elen.\"\n\nThe silence is softer now--not the hush of danger, but the brief calm that follows victory. Somewhere below, a jay calls, and the scent of new grass pushes back against the lingering scent of burnt moss.\n\nWhat will you do? Rest and recover, search the Nexus for anything left untended, or set out immediately for Harrow's Hollow in search of your friends?",
